    {
      "id": 76,
      "label": " Anxiety and shock",
      "parent_id": 0,
      "description": "A person has emotional distress or sudden fright, their body releases adrenaline into the bloodstream, but this usually reverses itself in a healthy person. This is where the confusion in the term ‘shock’ sometimes occurs. This ‘non-medical shock’ is a response to anxiety or fear."
    },
