    {
      "id": 1,
      "label": "Abscesses and boils",
      "parent_id": 0,
      "description": "Boils are usually small areas (penny or nickel size) with a thin covering of skin, while abscesses are larger raised areas on the skin that are tender to touch and filled with pus in the deeper tissue.\\r\\nAbscesses and boils may drain when the skin over the infected area opens and lets the fluid or pus out.\\r\\nAn abscess under your skin is easy to see. It may appear red, raised and swollen. The skin over the centre of the abscess may be thin. It may look yellow or white because there’s pus underneath the surface of your skin. The abscess may feel tender and warm to the touch. Other symptoms of a skin abscess include pain, fever and chills."
    },
