      "id": 66,
      "label": "Allergies Seasonal",
      "parent_id": 0,
      "description": "An itch is an unpleasant tingly sensation that makes you want to scratch. If you’re allergic to poison ivy and you go hiking through a field of it, you’ll have a terrible itch all over your legs.\\r\\n\\r\\nMany people find relief with self-care measures such as moisturizing daily, using gentle cleansers and bathing with lukewarm water. Long-term relief requires identifying and treating the cause of itchy skin."
